
More Loops and Iterators Worksheet
Read the code in each section, then write exactly what the code prints out.

Each problem stands alone. Variables from previous problems do not exist.

Example:

x = 5
y = 6
print(x+y)
# => 11

Problem Set
cars = ["old", "new", "used"]
cars.each do |car|
  puts car
end
Answer: old
        new
        used

fruits = ["banana", "apple", "kiwi"]
fruits.each do |fruit|
  puts "I love " + fruit + "!"
end

Answer: I love banana!
        I love apple!
        I love kiwi!
        
values = [8, 5, 3, 10, 14, 2]
values.each do |value|
  puts value
end
Answer: 8
        5
        3
       10
       14
        2

total = 0
values = [4, 6, 2, 8, 11]

values.each do |value|
    total = total + value
end
puts total

Answer: 31 

values = [8, 5, 3, 10, 14, 2]
values.each do |value|
  if value == 10
    puts "Special case!"
  else
    puts "Regular values like #{value}"
  end
end

Answer: Regular values like 8
        Regular values like 5
        Regular values like 3
        Special case!
        Regular values like 14
        Regular values like 2
